  <refsect1 xml:id="description"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
  <para>The <command>g-voxel</command> command generates a list of voxels from a .g file (BRL-CAD database)
  and writes them to a voxels.txt file.</para>

  <para>The command takes two compulsory arguments: a BRL-CAD database and at least one
  geometry object (though there can be as many of the latter as you like).</para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 xml:id="options"><title>OPTIONS</title>
  <variablelist remap="IP">
    <varlistentry>
      <term><option>-s "dx dy dz"</option></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>The voxel's size in the x, y and z axes.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><option>-d n</option></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>The level of detail used (influences the number of rays used).</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><option>-t f</option></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>The threshold upon which the voxel is considered.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

